      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(whatsapp): add listGroupsLive for real-time group directory",
        "body": "## Root Cause\n\nThe WhatsApp channel directory adapter only registered `listGroups` (which reads from the config map `channels.whatsapp.groups`) but did **not** register `listGroupsLive`. The CLI (and other consumers) prefer `listGroupsLive` when available, so users who have active WhatsApp group memberships but an empty config-based groups map would see an empty directory. No `listGroupsLive` implementation existed for WhatsApp.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Bug: WhatsApp directory `/groups` returned empty even when the account is a member of groups, because only the config-backed `listGroups` was wired up but not the live-fetch variant.\n- This PR adds `listWhatsAppDirectoryGroupsLive` that fetches groups from the Baileys socket via `groupFetchAllParticipating()`, with graceful fallback to config when the socket is unavailable or throws. The new function is registered in the channel directory adapter.\n- Fixes #76722\n\n## Revision (2026-06-20)\n\n- Fixed a P2 issue where live groups were filtered by JID only, so `--query \"Family\"` would not match a group named \"Family Chat\". Now builds entries first and filters by both JID and subject name (matching Discord/Slack live directory behavior).\n- Commit: `e7ac40ee0e`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test extensions/whatsapp/src/directory-config.test.ts` — 8/8 passed (6 new tests + 2 existing; +1 test for name-based filtering)\n- `pnpm tsgo:test` — passed (type check)\n- `pnpm lint:extensions:bundled` — passed\n- Autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n- CI: The `checks-node-core-tooling` failure is an infrastructure/flaky issue unrelated to this PR (only touches `extensions/whatsapp/`)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: WhatsApp directory `/groups` now returns the account's real group memberships fetched live from the WhatsApp connection, filtered by both JID and group name.\nReal environment tested: Linux, Node 22, branch `fix/issue-76722-whatsapp-directory-groups-live` commit `e7ac40ee0e`\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n```bash\npnpm test extensions/whatsapp/src/directory-config.test.ts\npnpm tsgo:test\npnpm lint:extensions:bundled\n```\nEvidence after fix:\n```console\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/whatsapp/src/directory-config.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  8 passed (8)\n   Start at  00:50:52\n   Duration  25.63s\n```\nObserved result after fix: All 8 tests pass including the new test for name-based query filtering. Type check and lint pass cleanly.\nWhat was not tested: Live E2E with a real WhatsApp account (requires Crabbox with WhatsApp auth); no WhatsApp directory binary/E2E test infrastructure exists.\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-76722-whatsapp-directory-groups-live",
